Question 1.

Steps in evolutuion of the plot:The plot starts off as a standard boxplot -The plot is then rotated on its side to make it easier to interpret the different levels of student to teacher ratio. -Then the graph is made transparent and colour is added to make it more appealing to general audience. -It is then converted to a violin plot which is a good way to show the distribution of each of the continents in this case. -Then its changed into a dot plot which in my opinon isnt a suitable plot -Dots are then made transparent and the original box plot graph is overlayed on it -The dots are then changed to a scatter plot format to show the variation in the box plot - Box plot overlay is removed and a big point to indicate the mean is added to the scatter plot - A line indicating the worldwide average is added to the plot and then a range is also added to indicate how above or below each continent is from the average -Labels are added to the plot indicating where the continental average is , the countries per continent and where outliers exist i.e the Central afircan republic has the most students per teacher.
